Question: what are bhagwan chowdhry's responsibilities at isb?
Answer:
Prof. Bhagwan Chowdhry holds significant responsibilities at the Indian School of Business (ISB), particularly in fostering entrepreneurship and nurturing startups. Here are some of his key roles:

- **Faculty Director of I-Venture @ ISB**: In this capacity, Prof. Chowdhry oversees the initiatives that support entrepreneurship at ISB. This includes administering business incubators and facilitating the transformation of startups into successful entrepreneurial ventures.

- **Mentorship and Guidance**: He is involved in drafting alumni members as mentors to help nurture startup ideas into scalable businesses. This mentorship plays a crucial role in providing both strategic and practical guidance to budding entrepreneurs.

- **Global Startup Ecosystem Integration**: Prof. Chowdhry is instrumental in creating a global corridor for startups, which helps Indian startups to explore and expand into international markets and vice versa. This initiative is aimed at enhancing the global reach of startups incubated at ISB.

- **Collaboration and Networking**: He works on engaging with various stakeholders within the entrepreneurship ecosystem, including other educational institutions, to host joint startup activities and bring teams together for collaborative opportunities.

- **Educational Initiatives**: Prof. Chowdhry is also involved in educational programs like the CM ST Entrepreneurship and Innovation (CMSTEI) scheme, which supports and promotes entrepreneurship among scheduled tribes in Telangana, in collaboration with the Tribal Cooperative Finance Corporation (TRICOR).

Through these roles, Prof. Bhagwan Chowdhry significantly contributes to the entrepreneurial landscape at ISB, supporting both the growth of individual entrepreneurs and the broader startup ecosystem.

finchain
Accelerating Innovations in AI, Blockchain and DeFi 
Applications Closed 
About the Program 
 DLabs Incubator Association (DLabs) at the Indian School of Business (ISB), in collaboration with Broadridge, launches a global accelerator program for start-ups working in AI, Blockchain and DeFi space. The two organizations have come together to support and nurture innovations by offering comprehensive support, including mentorship, capacity building and networking opportunities. We empower startups working in different themes to thrive and attract the attention of relevant stakeholders and investors. 
Criteria 
Startups working in AI, Blockchain and DeFi thematic areas 
Minimum 1 year from incorporation 
Early revenue stage ventures with scalability potential 
Themes 
Use of AI in testing 
Generating insights from account and market information 
Foundational technology and infrastructure for Blockchain and DeFi ecosystems 
Integration of AI and Blockchain technologies in fintech 
Developing innovative decentralised applications on Blockchain platforms in fintech

Tailored Masterclasses & Workshops by Industry Experts 
​​Mentorship from DLabs and Broadridge 
Go-to-Market Strategies 
Fundraising Support

Piloting Opportunities

Networking 
Startup Toolkit

Program Partners

Contact Us 
contact@isbdlabs.org 
FAQs 
Who is eligible to apply for the FinChain @ ISB powered by Broadridge Acceleration Program?
Startups working in AI,  Blockchain and DeFi thematic areas, incorporated for a minimum of 1 year, at the post MVP stage or advanced product stage, and in the early revenue stage with scalability potential are eligible to apply.
What support does the program offer to selected startups?
The program offers comprehensive support, including mentorship from Dlabs and Broadridge, tailored masterclasses and workshops, business development,  go-to-market strategies, scale-up support, internationalisation support and strategic partnerships.
How long does the FinChain @ ISB powered by Broadridge Acceleration Program last?
The program has a timeline of approximately 9 weeks, including the acceleration period from January to March followed by a Demo day.
What happens after the application submission?
Shortlisted startups will be notified and provided with further instructions and details regarding their participation in the program.
Is the FinChain @ ISB powered by Broadridge Acceleration Program open to startups outside of India?
Yes, startups across the globe can apply
How can I get in touch for further inquiries?
For any further inquiries or questions, please feel free to contact us at contact@isbdlabs.org Our team will be happy to assist you and provide the necessary information.

cleantech-accelerator
Accelerating the Future of Sustainability 
Apply Now
 Application deadline: 31st August 2023 
About the Program 
AIC-Indian School of Business, presents a nationwide initiative dedicated to identifying and engaging exceptional entrepreneurs in the cleantech sector. This program aims to nurture ventures with innovative solutions to address environmental challenges in renewable energy, energy efficiency, climate tech, clean water, e-mobility, and green building. By offering comprehensive support, including mentorship, capacity building, field trials, and networking opportunities, we empower cleantech startups to thrive and attract the attention of relevant stakeholders and investors.Join us in driving sustainable change and building a greener future through the CleanTech Acceleration Program. 
Criteria

contact@aicisb.org 
Apply Now
FAQs 
Who is eligible to apply for the CleanTech Acceleration Program?
Startups incorporated for a minimum of 1 year, at the post MVP stage or advanced product stage (TRL 8-9), and in the early revenue stage with scalability potential are eligible to apply.
What support does the program offer to selected startups?
The program offers comprehensive support, including mentorship from AIC-ISB, tailored masterclasses and workshops, business development and market access assistance, field immersions, access to lab facilities, go-to-market strategies, market access and scale-up support, internationalization support, strategic partnerships
How long does the CleanTech Acceleration Program last?
The program has a timeline of approximately 3 months, including the acceleration period from August to October. It also includes a Demo Day event in November for startups to showcase their progress and accomplishments.
What happens after the application submission?
After the application submission, the shortlisting and onboarding process will take place in July and August. Shortlisted startups will be notified and provided with further instructions and details regarding their participation in the program.
Is the CleanTech Acceleration Program open to startups outside of India?
No, the CleanTech Acceleration Program is specifically designed for startups incorporated in India. It is not open to startups from outside of India.
How can I get in touch for further inquiries?
For any further inquiries or questions, please feel free to contact us at contact@aicisb.org. Our team will be happy to assist you and provide the necessary information.
